      p.lead Open Budget: Oakland visualizes the city's current and past budget data into accessible charts for the public. Data is published by the city. See Oakland's #[a(href='/budget-visuals.html') previous budgets], as well as the city's #[a(href='https://www.oaklandca.gov/documents/fiscal-year-2019-20-to-2023-24-five-year-financial-forecast' target='_blank') five-year forecast].

      .well
        h3.blurb__title Mayor's 2019-21 Proposed Budget
        p The mayor's office released a #[a(href='https://data.oaklandnet.com/Financial/FY-2019-21-Biennial-Proposed-Budget/aeya-c8st' target='_blank') proposed policy budget] for fiscal years 2019 - 2020 and 2020 - 2021 in May 2019. The City Council approved a final (adopted) budget at the June 24th City Council meeting.

      p
        h3.blurb__title Did you know&hellip;
        p you can create your own visualizations with our free #[a(href='https://github.com/openoakland/openbudgetoakland/wiki/API-Documentation') Open Budget Oakland API]?

